      <shortdescription><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://eclipse.org/vex"><strong>Vex</strong></a> is a <strong>V</strong>isual <strong>E</strong>ditor for <strong>X</strong>ML that hides the raw XML tags from the user, providing instead a <strong>word processor like</strong> interface. Vex uses standard <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Document_Type_Definition">DTD</a>/<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XML_Schema_%28W3C%29">XSD</a> files to define document types and <strong>CSS</strong> to define document layout. Vex contains built-in support for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Docbook">DocBook</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DITA">DITA</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Docbook">XHTML</a>. To edit other XML formats only a DTD/XSD and a CSS are needed.</p>
<p>See also: <a href="http://vimeo.com/58346326">Video: "Vex - Getting Started"</a></p>
]]></shortdescription>
